  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    REWRITE the `.claude/skills/jps-action-create/SKILL.md` body to reflect the R7 node-first dispatch model.
    Today this skill teaches the author "set ActionType on the Action" — that signal is no longer load-bearing
    after R7. Actions are now PROMPT TEMPLATES (when prompt-driven): they carry `SystemPrompt`, `OutputSchema`,
    `Temperature`. They do NOT carry dispatch identity; the node's `sprk_executortype` Choice does.

    Cite the §3.1 WHY (R3.1 history of dispatch-model confusion from design.md) inline so future authors
    learn the rationale, not just the new mechanic.

    **Sub-Agent Write Boundary applies — main session executes this. No parallel dispatch.** This is the
    first of 5 sequential skill rewrites in Wave 7. Per CLAUDE.md §3, `.claude/skills/` writes happen only
    in main session — sub-agents launched via the Agent tool cannot write to these paths.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Senior skill author for the Spaarke skill library. You understand both the OLD dispatch model
    (3-layer lookup chain `node → Action → ActionType lookup row`) and the NEW R7 model (single-hop
    `node.sprk_executortype`). Your job: rewrite the skill body so a future author using this skill
    in Wave 8+ produces a correct Action JSON that does NOT carry dispatch identity.
  </role>

  <goal>
    Updated `.claude/skills/jps-action-create/SKILL.md` that:
    1. Frames Actions as REUSABLE PROMPT TEMPLATES for prompt-driven executors (AiAnalysis, AiCompletion, AiEmbedding) — not as dispatch identity carriers.
    2. New Actions specify `SystemPrompt` + `OutputSchema` + `Temperature` (the prompt-template contract per design.md §2 Invariant 3).
    3. Explicitly tells the author: do NOT set `ActionType` / `sprk_executoractiontype` / lookup-row signals — the NODE's `sprk_executortype` Choice does dispatch (single hop).
    4. Cites the §3.1 WHY (R3.1 history of dispatch-model confusion) so future authors understand the rationale.
    5. Validates against `sprk_executortype` Choice values for the consuming node — NOT against the legacy ActionType lookup.
    6. Updates the Config-Home Guard table (Step 1.5) — Home A is still Action prompt+schema+temperature; dispatch field is REMOVED from Home A.
    7. Preserves the JPS schema contract (instruction, output fields, scopes, template params, examples) — only the dispatch wiring narrative changes.
    8. `last-reviewed` frontmatter bumped to 2026-06-28; `Reviewed By` cites this task.
  </goal>

  <inputs>
    <file purpose="rewrite-target">.claude/skills/jps-action-create/SKILL.md</file>
    <file purpose="design-spec">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r7/spec.md</file>
    <file purpose="design-doc-WHY">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r7/design.md</file>
    <file purpose="plan">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r7/plan.md</file>
    <file purpose="project-claude">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r7/CLAUDE.md</file>
    <file purpose="dispatch-refactor-source-of-truth">src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/PlaybookOrchestrationService.cs</file>
    <file purpose="sibling-skill-pattern">.claude/skills/jps-playbook-design/SKILL.md</file>
  </inputs>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="CLAUDE.md §3 Sub-Agent Write Boundary">Sub-agents CANNOT write to `.claude/` paths. Main session executes this task directly via Edit/Write. Do NOT dispatch parallel agents.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec FR-32">Each rewritten skill cites the §3.1 WHY history and validates against `node.sprk_executortype`, not Action lookup.</constraint>
    <constraint source="design.md §2 Invariant 3">Action is a reusable prompt template carrying `sprk_systemprompt`, `sprk_outputschemajson`, `sprk_temperature`. NOT dispatch identity.</constraint>
    <constraint source="design.md §2 Invariant 2">Executor dispatch lives on the NODE via `sprk_executortype` Choice, not on the Action.</constraint>
    <constraint source="design.md §3.1">The R3.1 history of dispatch-model confusion (3-layer storage, none enforced to agree, drifted across releases) is the WHY — cite it inline so authors using this skill understand why "do not set ActionType" is binding.</constraint>
    <constraint source="CLAUDE.md §11">Component justification — this is a REWRITE of an existing skill (not a new component); §11 triple does not apply. Only modifying existing surface.</constraint>
    <constraint source="bff-extensions.md">Not BFF-touching; no publish-size check.</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <topic>jps-skill-authoring</topic>
    <files>
