      </pattern>
      <pattern name="WHY-citation inline" location="design.md §3.1">
        Brief inline reference: "Why no dispatch signal on Action? See R3.1 — the 3-layer dispatch storage caused every release to ship a different version of the same bug."
      </pattern>
    </patterns>
  </knowledge>

  <context>
    <background>
      Wave 7 (FR-32, FR-33) rewrites jps-* skill bodies to teach the R7 dispatch model. Wave 2 task 024
      shipped the single-hop dispatch refactor in the BFF; Wave 5 backfilled the 94 existing nodes;
      this wave aligns the skill instructions so future authors don't recreate the legacy split.

      jps-action-create is the FIRST skill rewrite — it authors new Action JPS definitions. The downstream
      skills (jps-playbook-design, jps-playbook-audit, jps-validate) build on the new Action contract.
    </background>
    <dependencies>
      <dependency task="024" status="prerequisite">Wave 2 single-hop dispatch refactor must be merged; the runtime now reads `node.sprk_executortype` only.</dependency>
    </dependencies>
    <related-work>
      <item>Tasks 071-073 rewrite the sibling jps-* skills; task 074 minor-updates jps-scope-refresh; task 075 runs `/jps-validate` for smoke-test.</item>
      <item>Wave 6 task 065 (MAJOR UPDATE JPS-AUTHORING-GUIDE.md) updates the operator guide in `docs/guides/`. Skill body + guide must stay aligned.</item>
    </related-work>
  </context>

  <steps>
    <step order="0" name="Rigor Declaration">
      Output: 🔒 RIGOR LEVEL: STANDARD · 📋 REASON: skill body rewrite (not ADR-bound code); STANDARD per CLAUDE.md §8 — no Step 9.5 code-review/adr-check · Proceeding with Step 0...
    </step>
    <step order="1" name="Load context">
      Read project CLAUDE.md + spec.md FR-32 + design.md §2 Invariants 1-3 + §3.1 WHY history.
    </step>
    <step order="2" name="Read existing skill body">
      Read full current `.claude/skills/jps-action-create/SKILL.md`. Note: frontmatter, Purpose, Applies When, Step 1.5 Config-Home Guard, Step 2+ workflow steps, examples references.
    </step>
    <step order="3" name="Inventory legacy dispatch references">
      Grep the skill body for references to: `ActionType`, `sprk_actiontypeid`, `sprk_executoractiontype`, "action type lookup", "lookup row", "dispatch on Action". List every reference; each must be rewritten or deleted.
    </step>
    <step order="4" name="Rewrite Purpose + Applies When">
      Reframe: "Creates a new reusable prompt template (JPS Action) for prompt-driven executors. The Action carries SystemPrompt + OutputSchema + Temperature. The NODE that consumes this Action carries dispatch identity via `sprk_executortype` (single hop, set in PlaybookBuilder)."
    </step>
    <step order="5" name="Update Config-Home Guard table (Step 1.5)">
      Home A row: "Action-intrinsic — prompt + output schema + default temperature". DELETE any dispatch-field mention from Home A.
      Add inline WHY: "Dispatch was REMOVED from Home A in R7. The node's `sprk_executortype` Choice owns dispatch identity per design.md §2 Invariant 2. Why? See §3.1 — the 3-layer dispatch storage caused every release to ship a different version of the same class of bug."
    </step>
    <step order="6" name="Update workflow steps">
      Remove any step that asks the author to set ActionType or executor on the Action. The JPS workflow stays — only the dispatch wiring is removed. The Action JPS still defines instruction, output fields, scopes, template params, examples.
    </step>
    <step order="7" name="Add a R7 dispatch-model context section">
      Insert a short subsection (~15 lines): "## The R7 dispatch model — what changed and why" citing design.md §3.1 + §2 Invariants 1-3. Make the WHY explicit so future authors learn the rationale, not just the new mechanic.
    </step>
    <step order="8" name="Update validation guidance">
      Where the skill previously validated Action JSON against an ActionType lookup, replace with: "Validate against the consuming node's `sprk_executortype` Choice. The Action JSON itself does not carry dispatch identity."
    </step>
    <step order="9" name="Bump frontmatter">
      `last-reviewed: 2026-06-28`; `Reviewed By: spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r7 task 070 (FR-32 — node-first dispatch rewrite)`.
    </step>
    <step order="10" name="Verify acceptance">
      Re-read the rewritten skill body. Confirm: (a) no remaining ActionType-on-Action language, (b) §3.1 WHY is cited inline at least once, (c) Config-Home Guard table updated, (d) Purpose + Applies When reframed, (e) frontmatter bumped.
    </step>
    <step order="11" name="Update current-task.md + TASK-INDEX">
      Mark task 070 status complete; advance current-task.md to task 071.
    </step>
    <step order="12" name="Commit-deferred">
      DO NOT commit. Wave 7 commits as a single PR after task 075. Stage changes locally; main session commits at wave-end.
    </step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
    <tool>Read (existing skill body + design.md + spec.md)</tool>
    <tool>Grep (legacy ActionType references in skill body)</tool>
    <tool>Edit (rewrite skill body sections in place)</tool>
